  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial: necessary-sufficient confusion)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package contains a subtle sufficiency-confusion weakener: the decision rationale elevates the RH < 1 acceptance criterion on the Output Comparison factor to a sufficient condition for the overall CPB safety goal, while other assessed factors (model form uncertainty, discretization error, model inputs) that are independently necessary are not addressed in the rationale.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-rh-index-sufficient-for-cpb-safety",
